# Child and Adolescent Mental Health

Educational notes on mental health in children and adolescents, aimed at clinicians, residents, and students.

## Purpose
- Outline common mental health conditions in youth
- Support clinical reasoning and developmental assessment
- Provide structured, accessible content in Portuguese

## Planned subtopics
- Anxiety and depression in children and adolescents
- Behavioral disorders and disruptive behaviors
- Neurodevelopmental conditions
- Self-harm and suicide risk in youth
- Family and school context in assessment
- General principles of treatment and support

> Note: Content in this repository is for educational purposes only and does not replace formal clinical training, local protocols, or individualized medical care.
